President Trump expressed gratitude to General Brooks and the people working on the situation in South Korea. He chose to eat with the troops instead of having a fancy lunch and praised their work. He mentioned his successful visit to Japan and his upcoming visit to China. Trump also mentioned a trade meeting with President Moon and discussions with various generals about the situation in North Korea. He expressed confidence that things will work out in the end. He thanked everyone for being there and mentioned a separate meeting later in the day.